        {
            "_id": "trqX63UZszcbyF86",
            "img": "systems/pf2e/icons/default-icons/action.svg",
            "name": "Pour Elixir",
            "sort": 800000,
            "system": {
                "actionType": {
                    "value": "action"
                },
                "actions": {
                    "value": 3
                },
                "category": "offensive",
                "description": {
                    "value": "<p><strong>Requirements</strong> Aron has a physical body</p>\n<p><strong>Frequency</strong> twice per day</p><hr /><p><strong>Effect</strong> Aron forms a pitcher in one hand from ectoplasm, then pours liquid from the pitcher out onto a solid surface. As the liquid pours, it forms into a single glass vial filled with an alchemical elixir of Aron's choice. He's always willing and eager to Pour an Elixir for the PCs when asked. An elixir created by this ability vanishes if not used within 24 hours of being poured. He can choose from the following options when he uses Pour Elixir: @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.equipment-srd.Item.Antidote (Moderate)]{Moderate Antidote}, @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.equipment-srd.Item.Antiplague (Moderate)]{Moderate Antiplague}, @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.equipment-srd.Item.Darkvision Elixir (Moderate)]{Moderate Darkvision Elixir}, @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.equipment-srd.Item.Eagle Eye Elixir (Moderate)]{Moderate Eagle Eye Elixir}, or @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.equipment-srd.Item.Elixir of Life (Lesser)]{Lesser Elixir of Life}.</p>\n<p><strong>Rank 2</strong> Aron's elixirs are now greater versions rather than moderate (or in the case of an elixir of life, a moderate one instead of a lesser one).</p>\n<p><strong>Rank 3</strong> Aron can now Pour Elixir three times a day, and his elixirs of life are now greater elixirs of life.</p>"
                },
                "frequency": {
                    "max": 2,
                    "per": "day"
                },
